sentences: René Dif (born 17 October 1967) is a Danish musician, singer-songwriter, DJ and actor, best known as the male lead vocalist of the Danish-Norwegian eurodance group Aqua.

sentences: Dif met Lene Nystrøm on a cruise ship in 1994.
Aqua's main hits were "Roses Are Red", "My Oh My", "Barbie Girl", "Lollipop (Candyman)", "Doctor Jones", "Turn Back Time", "Good Morning Sunshine", "Cartoon Heroes" and "Around the World".
Following Aqua's split in 2001, Dif released solo singles, including "Let it all out (Push it)" and "The Uhh Uhh Song".
In 2004 he began a career as an actor, starring in several movies directed by Lasse Spang Olsen.
In 2002 he published an autobiography titled Popdreng – Ud af skabet.
Aqua reunited in 2008 as a live band.

In March 2011, Aqua released the first single, "How R U Doin?", from their third album Megalomania, released in September 2011 following the release of two more singles, "Playmate to Jesus" and "Like a Robot".

Rene Dif was in a relationship with fellow Aqua band member Lene Nystrøm, whom he invited to join the band in 1994.
They were in a relationship for three years, before they broke up.
He is now in a relationship with Linet Jo.
